se or the world at large. Try not to see your condition as an illness so much as a difference or a handicap that can be overcome. Have you heard of cognitive therapy? try google if you have not.</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109943263381654001/comments/default/6047325075987055309'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109943263381654001/comments/default/6047325075987055309'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/11/word-about-violence-revenge.html?showComment=1183293840000#c6047325075987055309' title=''/><author><name>red-dingo</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/blank.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/11/word-about-violence-revenge.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109943263381654001' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109943263381654001' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-152740699"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="5:44 AM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-3106759884293927280</id><published>2007-06-03T23:58:00.000-07:00</published><updated>2007-06-03T23:58:00.000-07:00</updated><title type='text'>As a woman, the one thing that scares me the most ...</title><content type='html'>As a woman, the one thing that scares me the most about being homeless is violence and rape. I am not homeless yet, but I have mental illness and it seems to be getting worse, so I read up on sites like this just in case I cannot work anymore. Also with gas prices the way they are lately 6/3/2007, I don&#39;t know if I would be able to afford vehicle living. Maybe one day I can get SS